node.text:
At this point, it’s not quite accurate to say there’s a crisis at the border. The situation is much worse than that. As a result of the policy changes enacted by Joe Biden, combined with an utter lack of planning or foresight about what those policies would produce, the border is now in chaos — and getting worse by the day.

Seems like everything Joe Biden touches turns to 💩

#usbp #borderpatrol #buildthewall #securetheborder #maga #makeamericagreatagain #bordercrisis #bidenbordercrisis #bidensucks #democratsdestroyamerica

node.text:
Several top officials from the ousted Western-backed government have gathered in the Panjshir Valley. They include Vice President Amrullah Saleh, who claims to be the caretaker leader after President Ashraf Ghani fled the country.

They have vowed to resist the Taliban and are calling for Western aid to help roll them back.

Most people don’t know that the VP of Afghanistan did not flee the country, but instead fled into the Panjshir Valley. 

“I watched this.  This man wants strength from the US.  Biden has shown the entire world he is WEAK.  My fears are we will have another 9/11 or worse. Biden lied saying the the Afghan soldiers gave up.  I am sick of Lyin Biden. When will people and those that are to represent us stand up, grow a set, and get down to business.  We have got to get OUR people out of Afghanistan and those that helped our troops. Joe Biden, Kamela Harris, Nancy Pelosi need to be removed from their respective offices and held for Treason.  Over 85 BILLION dollars of weapons were handed over to the enemy.  Not to mention the names of those who helped us. “

node.title: VP of Afghanistan wants strength from the U.S. but gets WEAKNESS

node.text:
NYPD Officer Moira Smith was the first person to report the 9/11 attack. She immediately ran into the towers and started evacuating people. She was last seen going back into the south tower to evacuate more people. After the collapse of the second tower, there was a brief radio transmission from a female officer calling for help. It was later determined that this radio call was from Officer Smith. Her remains were recovered in March 2002. She was the only female NYPD officer to die at Ground Zero.
